===Glyph origin===
{{Han etym}}
{{liushu|p}} – a figure with two lines {{zh-l|上}} for a head (one connected to body, one above it), emphasizing the head.

===Etymology 1===
Possibly from {{cog-lite|sit-pro|*m/s-gaw||head}}, with a noun-forming suffix ''*-n'' ({{zh-ref|Schuessler, 2003}}; STEDT). If so, cognate with {{och-l|后|id=1|gloss=ruler; lord; queen}}, {{cog-lite|bo|sc=Tibt|མགོ||tr=mgo|head; summit; beginning}}, {{m|bo|མགོན||protector; master; lord}}, {{cog-lite|grt|sko||skull}}, {{cog|tji|kho⁵⁵ pa⁵⁵||head}} ({{zh-ref|Schuessler, 2007}}; STEDT). {{och-l|原|gloss=source; origin; basic; primary}} and {{och-l|黿|gloss=large turtle}} may be the same word ({{zh-ref|Schuessler, 2007}}). It may also be related to {{och-l|君|gloss=lord; prince; ruler}}, {{och-l|尹|gloss=magistrate; governor}}, {{och-l|侯|gloss=marquis}} ({{zh-ref|Mei, 1985}}). Possibly related to {{och-l|圓|gloss=round, sky}}.

The name of the dynasty comes from the ''{{w|I Ching}}'':
: {{zh-x|大 哉 乾{qián} 元，萬物 資 始，乃 統 天。|Vast is the ‘'''great and originating (power)'''’ indicated by Qian! All things owe to it their beginning: - it contains all the meaning belonging to (the name) heaven.|ref=Yijing-L|collapsed=y}}

Part of the people with this surname are {{w|Xianbei}} descendants. It was changed from {{zh-m|拓跋}} as ordered by {{w|Emperor Xiaowen of Northern Wei}}.

